page.title: 16SOME WELL-KNOWN PEOPLE
page.content: Mr Jeacock is a journalist who writes in the paper about his life on the Fen. Sir Brian Matthews is an inventor who in the Second World War he and another person ivented an ejector seat for an aeroplane. Also he has an eletricity generator in his garden which he has made.Mr Garstin was a doctor in Belsen (West Germany) and he made a programme a little while ago called "Doctors in Belsen" on BBC2 about what he did in Belsen and what it was like.Mr Hanke is a botanist who studies in something that only four other people in the world study. Mr Bourne is an architect who designs most of the buildings in Swaffham Bulbeck.Professor F.Sanger is a Nobel Prize Winner (1958 and 1980) and used to be on the staff of the Medical Research Council.
